  "warning": "{\"blocks\":[{\"key\":\"e0q3l\",\"text\":\"\",\"type\":\"unstyled\",\"depth\":0,\"inlineStyleRanges\":[],\"entityRanges\":[],\"data\":[]}],\"entityMap\":{}}",
  "materials_text": "",
  "steps": [
    "Prepare end-point dilution series (10-fold serial dilutions, 5 to 6 levels).",
    "Monitor plates for lysis every few days, recording the number and position of clear wells on the plate.",
    "When clear or nearly clear wells no longer appear for 1 week, record the final “score” for each dilution level.",
    "Use the MPN Assay Analyser program (Passmore et al. 2000) to determine the most-probable-number (Taylor 1962) of infective phages in the lysate."
  ],
